						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of one <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> to the temple by Śīrāḷaṉ Nārāyaṇan, a <hi rend="italic">kaikkōḷa</hi> resident of Vikramaśōḻan-Vēḷam at Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśoḻapuram, for the daily supply of a (mud) pot for carrying water from the river for the sacred bath of the deity, at mid-day with the interest on the amount. </p>						

